Substantial modifications have been made to adapt it from the Codex engine to the
ZCode engine while keeping the Claude Code host layer:
  - The engine layer (scripts/lib/app-server.mjs, scripts/lib/zcode.mjs, the broker)
    was rewritten to speak the ZCode Protocol (reverse-engineered from `zcode app-server`)
    instead of the Codex app-server JSON-RPC protocol.
  - All slash commands, agents, skills, and prompts were rebranded from /codex:* to
    /zcode:* and from "Codex" to "ZCode".
  - /zcode:review runs as a read-only turn over collected git context (ZCode has no
    native reviewer); /zcode:transfer seeds a new ZCode session (ZCode exposes no
    session-import RPC).

This derivative work was written with ZCode (powered by the GLM-5.2 model from Z.ai)
and refined with human assistance.

